  <h1>🧑‍💻 About Me</h1>

  <p>
    Hey, I'm Humza Arshed Javaid — Maryland native (Leonardtown/Mechanicsville area), cloud architect, and Founding Architect at <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/humzajavaid">ElasticBin</a>. I design scalable infrastructure and mission-critical systems, mostly on AWS.
  </p>

  <p>
    Systems Engineering from UMBC. Before ElasticBin, I spent years at SMX (formerly Smartronix) building cloud solutions. Engineering is in the family — my dad, Arshed Javaid, co-founded Parraid after decades in telemetry and reliable systems.
  </p>

  <p>
    Certified: <strong>AWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional</strong> (2022) and <strong>AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty</strong> (2023). Heavy Terraform user for declarative IaC — provisioning, modules, state management, brownfield imports, and keeping environments reproducible and drift-free.
  </p>

  <p>
    Off the clock: back home, posting casual/spicy takes as <a href="https://x.com/humzinator">@humzinator</a> (Roti Mason: a bit more than curry), debating South Asian food, or just keeping it real. No hype, steady progress.
  </p>

  <p>
    Cloud infra, Terraform workflows, ML on AWS, roti recipes, or good vibes? Say hi on X or LinkedIn. 🚀
  </p>
